==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scion
<hw>Sci"on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>cion</ets>,
F. <ets>scion</ets>, probably from <ets>scier</ets> to saw, fr. L.
<ets>secare</ets> to cut. Cf. <er>Section</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A shoot or sprout of a plant; a
sucker.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A piece of a slender branch or twig cut
for grafting.</def> <mark>[Formerly written also cion, and
cyon.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, a descendant; an heir; <as>as, a
<ex>scion</ex> of a royal stock</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scioptic</ent>⟦br⟧
